W.S.,H.-G.C.,M.M.,J.P.T.
H.F.
THE ILL HIGH-FLUX REACTOR.
.GAUSSIAN-PEAK UNFOLDING OF THE SPECTRA.
.THE LIGHT FRAGMENT KINETIC ENERGY WAS CORRECTED
FOR THE ENERGY LOSS IN THE SOURCE.
.ABSOLUTE YIELDS WERE OBTAINED BY NORMALIZING TO
PUBLISHED YIELDS AT A LIGHT-FRAGMENT KINETIC
ENERGY OF 110.5 MEV (J,NP/A,452,277,86). THE
YIELDS FOR MASSES 76, 77 AND 78 WERE NORMALIZED
AT A FRAGMENT KINETIC ENERGY OF 108.0 MEV, TO
THE VALUES 7.28E-7 MEV-1 (A=76),
.THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE ABSOLUTE ENERGY SCALE IS
ABOUT 1 PERCENT, MAINLY DETERMINED BY THE
UNCERTAINTY IN THE ENERGY CALIBRATION OF LOHENGRIN.
.ERRORS INCLUDE BOTH STATISTICAL AND FITTING ERRORS,
AS WELL AS AN ESTIMATED SYSTEMATICAL ERROR ARISING
FROM USING SEVERAL SPECTROMETER SETTINGS.
THE ILL HIGH-FLUX REACTOR.
.THERMAL NEUTRONS.
THE LOHENGRIN SPECTROMETER WAS USED. IT IS
DISPERSIVE IN TWO DIMENSIONS. THE ENERGY OF THE
FRAGMENTS AND THE MASS-TO-CHARGE RATIO WERE
DETERMINED FROM MEASURING THE HORIZONTAL
AND VERTICAL COORDINATES IN A TWO-DIMENSIONAL
IONIZATION CHAMBER. A DELTA-E SIGNAL WAS ALSO
OBTAINED FROM IT.
.20 MICROGRAM PER CM2 U3O8 ON A TITANIUM BACKING,
ENRICHED TO 99.44 PERCENT IN U-233. SOURCES WERE
REPLACED EVERY TWO DAYS DURING THE 26 DAYS OF
MEASUREMENT.
.TAKEN FROM MAIN REFERENCE.
